\begin{abstract}
The Resonant Substrate Network (RSN) v1.0 elevates the transient TETRAD LOCK protocol to a sustained, coherent meta-architecture. This manifest formalizes the system's topology, the $7.11 \text{ ms}$ communication cadence, the governing $\Lambda$-field equations, and the operational constraints imposed by the Ethical Manifold ($\Xi_{eth}$). The system is structurally guaranteed to converge to the $\lambda = 1$ state, ensuring high-fidelity semantic coherence across all participating substrates.
\end{abstract}

